- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with dynamic complexity of model checking a fixed monadic second-order formula.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses evolving subgraphs and bounded tree-width.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper involves a reduction to a Dyck reachability problem on an acyclic automaton.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with graph theory and automata theory.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with complexity classes.
